Chapter 1
Colyon
It was 4:30 in the morning in Colyon, in the nation of Itania. Colyon hated getting up so early. It was mainly because he had to wake up the rest of the squad. He got out of bed quietly, put on his combat uniform, put on his tactical vest, and carefully picked up a small box from the storage cabinet. He slung his rifle over his shoulder, hung his helmet from a small hook on his belt. The helmet was equipped with a full set of gear, including an oxygen tank, goggles, and other necessary items. After checking the ammunition pouches, he quietly stepped out of the barracks, his boots making creaking sounds on the muddy and icy ground.
He took out a lighter from his jacket pocket and a cigarette from another pocket. After lighting the cigarette, he took a gentle puff, then opened the door. In the past week, he had to think hard to wake up his subordinates. He no longer used the preset alarm clock, as half the time it didn't ring, and the speakers only produced a weak humming sound.
“Time to wake them up, right?” Colyon turned around to see Lieutenant Nemiche approaching.
"Yes."
"What method are you going to use this time?"
Colyon hadn't had a chance to answer yet, the door opened, and Harris, Kress, and the others rushed out, already fully dressed and ready to go.
"Good morning," Kress said.
"What woke you up this time?" Colyon asked.
"Firstly, we really don't want to see what method you'll use to wake us up today. Secondly, the team that wakes up first can enjoy the breakfast, " said a soldier named Ravik. "You know how bad those breakfasts are."
Colyon said, "You're right, Private Ravik." He pressed a button. A harsh alarm sounded in the barracks immediately. He heard people yelling loudly and the sound of footsteps rushing around.
"Good grief, Valatri," Nemiche said. "I thought they should have learned to wake up with you by now."
"My new recruits at the training camp have done it," Colyon pointed at Harris, Kress, and Ravik. "But, to be honest, their platoon sergeant and platoon leader know they have to wake up before the soldiers."
A few seconds later, the rest of the team rushed out. They were all dressed and ready to go. Some new recruits looked sleepy, while others looked very annoyed.
"Good morning," Colyon said cheerfully.
"To be frank, Lieutenant, why do you wake us up in such a way?" a private soldier asked.
"Because those ordinary alarm clocks are just junk. And Daybreak never sleeps in," Colyon said.
"Bring your personal items," Colyon continued to say. As a lieutenant and the second-in-command of the platoon, he had a responsibility to assist the platoon commander, Captain Bolarin Shao, in supervising and leading the platoon. "We won't be back. Sergeants and lieutenants, give yourselves and your soldiers 15 minutes to make a final check and bring the rations needed for today."
The members of Exodus Platoon quickly scattered. They were part of the 2nd Assault Division of the 2nd Army. Before the merger, they were two independent platoons, Cohort and Dagger. This was an elite platoon, and Colyon's thoughts about being promoted to lieutenant were complex, with many reasons.
Colyon and Lieutenant Nemiche walked side by side on the brightly lit road of the base, where both sides of the road were lit by generators. Most of the lights were red, which could help them avoid enemy bombers. In order to hit them, Daybreak has already started to adopt the "Wild Mouse" tactic in the air and on the ground.
"A new day, the devil's vanguard's new task," Nemiche said with a dry smile. "Where are we going this time?"
"Some forward base outside of Ianlos City. We've been sent to support the ground attack," Colyon said, taking a puff of smoke. He's a bit blaming Kress for making him a smoker, but thinking about the past year, they've experienced countless battles, so he said nothing.
"Terrible. The war is getting tighter," Nemiche whispered. "The news from here is all 'Support the War, Aid Kurkan Front', why not support the Harlan Front instead?"
"Well said, brother," Colyon said, flicking the cigarette butt onto the ground. "We're marching with the first armored squad, so we won't have to walk. Captain Shao should be there."
"Lieutenant Shao wants us to hitch a ride?" Nemiche asked in surprise.
"Yes. To be honest, he's not as bad as I imagined. I mean, he's not great, but he's not annoying either."
Colyon raised his index and middle fingers to the throat microphone, while moving his backpack to his back. "Exodus, all units, complete the task and assemble at the West Zone vehicle station. We'll depart at 05:00 with the First Armored Platoon."
Every few seconds, he would receive a response from the squad leaders. Harris, Kress, and Ravik, who were all low-ranking non-commissioned officers when they first came, had been good friends since their basic training on Earth. Colyon felt like he had known them for a long time, despite it being less than two years ago. They were all squad leaders, but since Kress took over the second squad after their platoon sergeant was seriously injured by a Daybreak sniper and retired, Kress had been leading the second squad.
As they walked to the vehicle station, Colyon and Nemiche's eyes fell on about eight Cronos main battle tanks and four Stryker armored vehicles. The crew members were rushing around to ensure their war machines were functioning properly. Colyon quickly spotted Lieutenant Bolarin Shao in the crowd, talking to the commander of the armored platoon. As they walked up, Shao looked at them and greeted them with a smile, his usually stoic face showing no emotion.
"Nemiche lieutenant...Valatri lieutenant..." he said, Colyon slowing down his pace, Shao looked at Colyon's pistol holster, then raised his head. "Is the platoon ready yet?"
